qas.question: What approximate percentage of carbon does wood have?
What element makes up about 6% of the chemical composition of wood?
About what percentage of wood is composed of nitrogen?
Which element in wood composes about 42% of its weight?
What element joins potassium, calcium, manganese, iron, and sodium to make a combined 1% of the chemical composition of wood?

context: The chemical composition of wood varies from species to species, but is approximately <a0_0>50%<a0_0/> carbon, 42% <a3_0>oxygen<a3_0/>, 6% <a1_0>hydrogen<a1_0/>, <a2_0>1%<a2_0/> nitrogen, and 1% other elements (mainly calcium, potassium, sodium, <a4_0>magnesium<a4_0/>, iron, and manganese) by weight. Wood also contains sulfur, chlorine, silicon, phosphorus, and other elements in small quantity.
